com.viaoa.html

Class OASession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.viaoa.html.OABase
      • com.viaoa.html.OASession
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class OASession
extends OABase
    Object used by one user. This has methods for storing Hubs and misc objects, adding forms, adding message, and keeping track of last page used, nextUrl to go to.
    See Also:
    OAApplication, Serialized Form

      • storeFrameUrl

        protected void storeFrameUrl(String formUrl,
                             OAFrame frame)
        called by OAFrame.setUrl() to store the URL of the Form or FrameSet that is assigned to the frame. Once the Form/FrameSet is created, it will call OASession.add(itself) and it will be assigned a Frame.
        Parameters:
        formUrl - is not case sensitive

      • bindCommand

        public void bindCommand(String formUrl,
                        String commandName,
                        String toFormUrl,
                        String toCommandName)
        this will automatically have a OACommand "press/submit" an OACommand on another form. A command can be bound to mutliple commands. A command will only be invoke if its form is currently being displayed.

      • bindCommand

        public void bindCommand(String formUrl,
                        String commandName,
                        String frameSetUrl,
                        String frameName,
                        String url)
        this will display a Url in a frame within a frameset when the OACommand or OALink is pressed/submitted.
        Parameters:
        formUrl - form that OACommand/OALink component is on
        commandName - name of OACommand/OALink component
        frameSetUrl - url of frameset that needs a new page displayed in one of its frames
        frameName - name of frame to display a page
        url - of new page to display
